creator: Bell, Charles Napier, 1854-1936.
description: Bell, Charles Napier: 1854-1936. From Ontario to Fort Garry as member of Wolseley expedition, fall 1870; after a year in Customs Department made hunting expedition in upper Saskatchewan region, summer 1872; customs clerk, 1874-1881; customs clerk with CPR, 1881-1886; secretary of Winnipeg Grain Exchange, 1887-1916; secretary-treasurer and later treasurer of Winnipeg Board of Trade, 1887-1919; active member of Historical and Scientific Society of Manitoba and other scientific societies (Winnipeg Free Press, August 3, 1936). // Also published as part of the 1888 Annual report of the Historical and Scientific Society of Manitoba , Winnipeg: Manitoba Free Press, 1889.
